            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Hd1e108">Rubrica 2</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De fortuitis aut fatalibus accidentibus aduersitatis vel prosperitatis</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>
      ¶ De fortuitis ac fatalibus accidentibus
      <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>aduersitatis vel prosperitatis. Rubrica 2. et
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e121">
               <lb ed="#V" n="28"/> <ref>ARistoteles etho. l. 2
      <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>c. 24.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e127">Ho
        <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>minibus multa cadunt non verisilia. fit
        <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>em quod praeter verisimile. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e135"> 
        <ref>/ Idem ethincorum
        <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>li. i. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e137">Multis contin gunt detrimenta ex bonis
        <lb ed="#V" n="33"/>Iam emim quidam pierunt perper diuitias. alii vero perper
        <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>fortitudinem.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e148"> 
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e150"> <ref>/ Idem magnorum moralium. li. i. c. i.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>A fortuna et diuitie fiunt: et pincipatus et vtilitur
        <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>quecumque in potentie ordinem conueniunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e158">
               <lb ed="#V" n="37"/> <ref>¶ Uirgilius enid. ti. 10 circa medium.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/> <quote>Ne scia mens hominum fati sortisque future. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e168">
               <lb ed="#V" n="39"/> <ref>¶ Tullius retho. artis noue. l. 5. c. 10.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e172">Omnia
        <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>subiecta sunt sub fortune dominatione. Erant qui
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>in prosperis fortune reus cunctos se putant fugis
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>se. Et non multum potest obesse fortuna qui sibi
        <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>firmius in virtute quam in casu praesidium colloca
        <lb ed="#V" n="44" break="no"/>uit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e186"> 
        <ref>/ Idem de amincitia.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e188">Non solum ipsa est
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>ceca fortuna: sed etiam plerumque efficit cecos <!--313.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>quos complexa est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e200">
               <lb ed="#V" n="47"/> <ref>¶ Seneca epistolarum ad lucilis vel. 13 e. 7. et p.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e204">Sa
        <lb ed="#V" n="48" break="no"/>piens vicit virtute fortunam.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e210"> 
        <ref>/ l. 18. e. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e212"> Nul
        <lb ed="#V" n="49" break="no"/>lus cont fortunam inexpugnabilis murus est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e219"> 
        <ref>/ l.
        <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>17. e. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e221">Erant qui aut boni aliquid nobis: aut
        <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>maliiudicant tribuere fortunam: mamm dat bo
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>norum et inicia rerum apud nos in malum bonumue
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>exiturarum. Ualentior enim omni fortuma ani
        <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>mus est: et in vtramque pertem ipse res suas ducit
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>beateque ac misere vite sibi causa est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e238">
               <lb ed="#V" n="56"/> <ref>/ Idem tragediarum in hyppolito. c. 10.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="57"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e242">Res humanas ordine nullo.
        <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>Fortuna regit: spargitque manu.
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>Munera ceca.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e252"> 
        <ref>/ In medea. c. 3</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="60"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e254">Fortuna opes auferre: non animum potest.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e260">
               <lb ed="#V" n="61"/> <ref>¶ Lex dig. ti. de minoribus. li. verum.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e264">Quod facto
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>contingit cui ius patrifamilias quamuis diligentis
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>simo potest contingere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e272"> 
        <ref>/ T. de administra. rerum
        <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>ad ciuitatem pertinem. l. 2. §. si eo tempore.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e274">Fortuitos casus nullum hominum consili
        <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>um prouidere potest.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e284">
               <lb ed="#V" n="67"/> <ref>¶ Lex cod. t de prescriptione. xxx. annorum.
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>l. fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e288">Sortes humane multe sunt: que nec di
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>ci nec enummerari possunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e297">
               <lb ed="#V" n="70"/> <ref>¶ Ualerius maximus vel. 7. t. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e301">Patet fortu
        <lb ed="#V" n="71" break="no"/>nam aduersas res cupido animo infligere:
        <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>secundas parco tribuere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e309">
               <lb ed="#V" n="73"/> <ref>¶ Fulgentius mitologiarum. in prohemiis.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e313">Felici
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>tatis nouerca fortuna est: que amarum quodam
        <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>humanis interserit: semper negociis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e321">
               <lb ed="#V" n="76"/> <ref>¶ Cato. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e325">Indulget fortuna malis: vt le
        <lb ed="#V" n="77" break="no"/>dere possit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e331"> 
        <ref>/ Capitulo. 5. et fi.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="78"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e333">Cum sis incautus nec rem ratione gubernes:
        <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>Noli fortunam que non est dicere cecam.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e341">
               <lb ed="#V" n="80"/> <ref>¶ Boetius de consolatione. l. 2. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e345">Fortuna
        <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>fingitur toqui hec verba: hec ntura vis est. hunc
        <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>continuum ludum lndimus. Rotam volubili orbe
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>versamus nunc insima summis: nunc summa infi
        <lb ed="#V" n="84" break="no"/>mis mutare gaudemus. Ascende si placet: sed
        <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>ea lege ne vti cum ludicri mei ratio poscet defe
        <lb ed="#V" n="86" break="no"/>re iniuriam putes. Quid tragediarum clamor
        <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>aliud deflet nisi indiscreto ictu fortunam feli
        <lb ed="#V" n="88" break="no"/>cia regna vertentem.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e366"> 
        <ref>/ 5. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e368">Rara est fortui
        <lb ed="#V" n="89" break="no"/>tis rebus manendi fides.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e375">
               <lb ed="#V" n="90"/> <ref>¶ Cassiodorus: epistolarum vel. 4. e. 47.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e379">Homines cum <!--314.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="138-r"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>tedere cupiunt beneficia frequenter imptiunt. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e391">
               <lb ed="#V" n="2"/> <ref>¶ Uersificator fabularum esopi. 42 fa.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e395">Cum lesit miseros fortunam medetur eisdem.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e401">
               <lb ed="#V" n="4"/> <ref>¶ Auctor vel qui dicitur pamphylus. c. 13</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="5"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e405">Obst tit interdum factis fortuna virorum.
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>Propositumque suo non sinit esse loco.
        <lb ed="#V" n="7"/>Sic nocuit multis: multos tantum illa beauit.
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>Uiuit in hoc mundo taliter omnis homo.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e417">
               <lb ed="#V" n="9"/> <ref>¶ Gualterius de castellione. l. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e421">Casus ruit
        <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>improuisus in omnes.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e427">
               <lb ed="#V" n="11"/> <ref>¶ Bertrandus hycon. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e431">Licet omnium rerum
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>mundanarum status et exitus negociorum sub for
        <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>tuna laborent: non tantu hoc timore est viuendi
        <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>regula omittenda.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e441"> 
        <ref>/ 24. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e443">Seruans doctrinam
        <lb ed="#V" n="15"/>raro accusabit fortunam: Raro diligentiam cum
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>infortunio sociabis. Sed rarius a pigritia
        <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>infortunium separabis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-d1e454">
               <lb ed="#V" n="18"/> <ref>¶ Prouer. vulg.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e05212-Qd1e458">Achi dio vol bene dorman
        <lb ed="#V" n="19" break="no"/>do geuene
        <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>Achi dio vol male le pegore ge da de dente
        <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>Achi dio vol male el ge tole elseno.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
